#: ../../I/ICBM-address.rst:5
msgid "ICBM address"
msgstr "ICBM address"

#: ../../I/ICBM-address.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../I/ICBM-address.rst:9
msgid ""
"(Also missile address) The form used to register a site with the Usenet "
"mapping project, back before the day of pervasive Internet, included a blank"
" for longitude and latitude, preferably to seconds-of-arc accuracy. This was"
" actually used for generating geographically-correct maps of Usenet links on"
" a plotter; however, it became traditional to refer to this as one's ICBM "
"address or missile address, and some people include it in their :ref:`sig-"
"block` with that name. (A real missile address would include target "
"elevation.)"
msgstr ""
"(missile "
"addressとも)インターネットが普及する以前、Usenetマッピングプロジェクトにサイトを登録するために使われた書式には、できれば秒角の精度での経度と緯度の記入欄が含まれていた。これは実際にはプロッタでUsenetリンクの地理的に正確な地図を生成するために使われていたのだが、これを自分のICBMアドレスやミサイルアドレスと呼ぶのが伝統となり、その名称で\\"
" :ref:`sig-block`\\ に含める人もいた。(本物のミサイルアドレスなら標的の標高も含むだろうが。)"
